\f1\b\fs48 \cf0 \strokec2 CHHAT Research Cigarette Brands / SKU Detection System\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 Technical Specification and Engineering Blueprint\
1. Executive position\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 This system should be built as a 
\f1\b computer-vision-first retail recognition platform
\f0\b0 , not an LLM-first image analyzer. The strongest architecture for shelf-product recognition remains: 
\f1\b detect packs \uc0\u8594  analyze cropped packs \u8594  combine OCR + visual matching + classification \u8594  use a VLM only for hard-case arbitration \u8594  send low-confidence cases to human review
\f0\b0 . That approach is aligned with retail-recognition research, which specifically highlights the value of 
\f1\b product-agnostic detection followed by similarity search / recognition on cropped items
\f0\b0 , and with newer fine-grained grocery-product work showing that 
\f1\b image + OCR text together
\f0\b0  outperform unimodal recognition for subtle product differences. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.01733"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 arXiv}})\
The system should be designed around two explicit goals:\
