\f1\b\fs48 \cf0 \strokec2 3. Non-negotiable architecture decisions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 3.1 Core architecture\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The production architecture should be:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf0 Image Ingest \uc0\u8594  Image QA \u8594  Pack Detection \u8594  Crop Normalization \u8594  OCR + Retrieval + Hierarchical Classification \u8594  VLM Arbitrator on hard cases \u8594  Fusion + Confidence Calibration \u8594  Auto-approve or Human Review \u8594  Active Learning \u8594  Scheduled Retraining
\f0\fs24 \
This is the best balance of scalability, cost control, and accuracy. The system should 
\f1\b not
\f0\b0  do direct whole-image classification as its primary method. Retail-recognition work supports the detect-then-recognize pattern, while multimodal grocery-product research supports combining package imagery with OCR-derived text. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.01733"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 arXiv}})\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 3.2 Model roles\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The models should be separated by role:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Detector
\f0\b0 : finds pack locations\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 OCR engine
\f0\b0 : extracts readable text from packs\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Retrieval encoder
\f0\b0 : matches crops to canonical SKU catalog\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Hierarchical classifier
\f0\b0 : predicts mother brand and then SKU within that brand family\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 VLM arbitrator
\f0\b0 : resolves hard cases only\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Fusion engine
\f0\b0 : produces final decision and confidence\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 This separation is necessary because box localization, fine-grained visual recognition, OCR extraction, and ambiguity reasoning are different tasks and should not be collapsed into one \'93smart model.\'94 ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.01733"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 arXiv}})\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 3.3 Accuracy philosophy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The system should not contract around one vague \'93overall accuracy\'94 number. It should measure:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 mother-brand presence F1\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 SKU presence F1\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 detection recall\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 counting error\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 unknown precision\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 review rate\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 calibration quality\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 That is the only defensible way to represent quality in a shelf-recognition system. The literature on grocery-product recognition makes clear that subtle SKU differences, wide orientation variation, and package text all materially affect performance. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00138-024-01549-9?utm_source=chatgpt.com"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Springer}})\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
